HEADWORD: Mousetail
<hw>Mouse"tail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus of ranunculaceous plants (<gen>Myosurus</gen>), in which
the prolonged receptacle is covered with imbricating achenes, and so
resembles the tail of a mouse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mouse trap</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>mousetrap</ent>⟦br⟧
